d tracking-tight text-white sm:text-3xl","children":"Most teams do not lack data. They lack a connected way to interpret it."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-4 max-w-4xl text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300 sm:text-base","children":"Growth reporting often starts simply. One dashboard covers paid search. Another tracks organic traffic. Lead totals live somewhere else. Executive reporting is assembled at the end. Over time, each piece becomes harder to connect. The result is not a data shortage. It is a visibility problem. This guide explains how that happens and what a clearer operating model can look like."}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mt-6 rounded-[28px] border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.04] p-6 lg:p-8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-emerald-300","children":"The Playbook"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-3xl","children":"Five ideas behind a clearer growth operating view"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid gap-4","children":[["$","div","Why fragmentation grows over time",{"className":"rounded-[24px] border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/70 p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white","children":"Why fragmentation grows over time"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300","children":"Teams add tools, channels, and reporting layers as complexity increases. Each addition solves a local problem while often making the total picture harder to interpret."}]]}],["$","div","Why channel visibility is not enough",{"className":"rounded-[24px] border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/70 p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white","children":"Why channel visibility is not enough"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300","children":"Channel dashboards are useful, but growth decisions often depend on what happens across channels, pages, funnel stages, and reporting periods together."}]]}],["$","div","Why funnel context changes the conversation",{"className":"rounded-[24px] border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/70 p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white","children":"Why funnel context changes the conversation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300","children":"Traffic and lead volume can look healthy while downstream performance weakens. Funnel visibility helps explain what top-line performance alone cannot."}]]}],["$","div","Why reporting should support decisions, not only updates",{"className":"rounded-[24px] border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/70 p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white","children":"Why reporting should support decisions, not only updates"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300","children":"The most useful reporting does more than summarize activity. It helps stakeholders understand what changed, why it matters, and where follow-up may be needed."}]]}],["$","div","Why prioritization matters as much as visibility",{"className":"rounded-[24px] border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/70 p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white","children":"Why prioritization matters as much as visibility"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300","children":"Even when teams can see the data, they still need help deciding what deserves attention first. Signals, alerts, and recommendation layers help create a more usable review process."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mt-6 rounded-[28px] border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.04] p-6 lg:p-8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-emerald-300","children":"Key Takeaways"}],["$","h2",null,{"clas